[[ Galapix ToDo ]]
_______________________________________________________________________________

Release procedure:
==================

* test that Galapix works with and without SpaceNavigator libraries

* test that all Galapix functions are accessible without SpaceNavigator

* test that mouse wheel is supported

* test svn trunk a lot

* test database compatibilty

* check that all keyboard shortcuts are documented and sort them a bit to be logical

* svn cp trunk@REV tags/galapix-0.0.X

Problems:
=========

* potential crash in JPEG::get_size(), current use of libjpeg might
  not be thread save (its not clear if the crash is caused by libjpeg,
  as it semes rather random):

(gdb) where
#0  0xb7a05fa7 in std::operator<< <char, std::char_traits<char>, std::allocator<char> > () from /usr/lib/libstdc++.so.6
#1  0x080a1c94 in JPEG::get_size (filename=@0x80574f2, size=@0xb46f8e48) at src/plugins/jpeg.cpp:57
#2  0xb7926ff4 in ?? () from /lib/tls/i686/cmov/libc.so.6
#3  0xb7926ff4 in ?? () from /lib/tls/i686/cmov/libc.so.6
#4  0xb77b805c in __pthread_mutex_unlock_usercnt (mutex=0x0, decr=134575346) at pthread_mutex_unlock.c:31
#5  0x00000000 in ?? ()

* need to handle mtime properly

* DatabaseThread is very similar to JobWorkerThread, maybe merge them

* galapix crashes when 

* maybe have something like JobHandle->spawn_child_job()

* current use of cURL is not thread safe due to curl_global_init()

* write tcl/tk script to convert old database to new database

* Quadtree stuff in Workspace could be speed up by recycling the
  std::vector object and by using marks on Image instead of a std::set
  to find things no longer on screen

* quality of small thumbnails is very bad, should start with larger
  thumbnails and then halve() them down instead of using scale()

* getting small tiles on startup should be much faster then getting
  them later, as it would need much less sql calls (one select vs one
  for each of thousands of pictures)

* shared_ptr<> impl is evil

* Database::tile_request_groups is never emptied

* viewdb -p PATTERN doesn't work as expected, as the viewer isn't updated in
  SDLViewer::run(), pressing '1' works as a workaround

* some jobs seem to stall and never get completed or never launched
  (TileRequest might be guilty)

* implement some proper stuff to report the current status (what jobs
  are running, what an image is doing, etc)

* add a is_queued() is_running() to the Job handle

* use highres tiles when they are in cache when zooming out (currently
  only using one level of highres data)

* make the database versioned by filename (easiest to implement):
  ~/.galapix/cache-1.sqlite

